               <p>JAMES IMLAH. I am a <rs id="t18180617-113-viclabel636" type="occupation">watchmaker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180617-113-victim987 t18180617-113-viclabel636"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18180617-113-crimeloc637">Grace-church-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18180617-113-crimeloc637" type="placeName" value="Grace-church-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18180617-113-crimeloc637" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18180617-113-off634 t18180617-113-crimeloc637"></join>. On the 20th of May I engaged the prisoner to clean the front of my shop, when he was gone I missed the tool - I had been using it the night before. I went to Mr. Styles's to buy another, and the first he produced to me was the one that I had lost.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. ARABIN. He had no rubbish to move.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18180617-113-person988">
                  JOHN 
                  NEWTON
               <interp inst="t18180617-113-person988" type="surname" value="NEWTON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180617-113-person988" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18180617-113-person988" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am servant to Mr. Styles, who keeps a tool warehouse, in Old-street. On the 21st of May the prisoner came and sold us the tool; he said he found it, and had had it by him sometime, and had endeavoured to find the owner, but could not.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. A woman who was at work with me, found it in the shop; she brought it away with the rubbish.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18180617-113-verdict638" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18180617-113-verdict638" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 39.</p>
